        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "FsWkG",
          "name": "About Content Wrapper",
          "width": "fill_container",
          "layout": "vertical",
          "gap": 32,
          "padding": [
            60,
            150
          ],
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "TytJY",
              "name": "H1",
              "fill": "$foreground-primary",
              "content": "About Joel Stransky",
              "fontFamily": "Playfair Display",
              "fontSize": 44,
              "fontWeight": "Bold"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "k6iPe",
              "name": "Paragraph 1",
              "fill": "$foreground-secondary",
              "content": "I am a Senior Software Engineer, UI/UX Designer, and Game Artist with over 30 years of experience developing interactive web applications. My work focuses on bridging the gap between interface design and front-end engineering architecture. I manage complex application state, design tokens, and browser-level runtime optimizations across various tech stacks, specializing in TypeScript, React, Next.js, SCSS, and monorepos.",
              "lineHeight": 1.6,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "xnlCC",
              "name": "Paragraph 2",
              "fill": "$foreground-secondary",
              "content": "My background includes engineering tools, framework standards, and custom browser extension components. At Konami Gaming, I replaced a legacy interface by implementing an open-source Chromium integration framework within a Java runtime, eliminating corporate software licensing fees and enabling native extension support for debugging. At College Loan Corporation, I consolidated six disparate platforms into a unified design system using variables and components in Figma, while optimizing layout performance to move site Google Lighthouse scores from C to A ratings.",
              "lineHeight": 1.6,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "nobhS",
              "name": "Paragraph 3",
              "fill": "$foreground-secondary",
              "content": "I have also developed reusable parent-theme architectures for the University of Hawaii and contributed to the ePib framework standard for the Barnes & Noble Nook Color rollout. My graphics and 3D engineering experience spans Game Art training at Full Sail University to building real-time client-server physics orchestration using TypeScript and React within Roblox. My current focus includes implementing Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers and structuring developer automation tools.",
              "lineHeight": 1.6,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "AEudi",
          "name": "Footer Section",
          "width": "fill_container",
          "stroke": "$border-subtle",
          "strokeWidth": {
            "top": 1
          },
          "padding": [
            32,
            80
          ],
